  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0bcb\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 24 \u0bae\u0ba3\u0bbf \u0ba8\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc6\u0b9f\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Quota has a 24 hour deadline",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Former President Maithripala Sirisena has said that it is the decision of the Sri Lanka Freedom Party that the Prime Minister and the President should submit to the people's vote and resign.",
        "The president of the Sri Lanka Freedom Party has stated in a statement that the president should resign within 24 hours, the prime minister should also resign, and after that all parties should be invited to form an all-party government.",
        "Today the President's Office and the Presidential Palace are occupied by people fighting for justice.",
        "The former President has said that his only demand is that President Gotabaya Rajapaksa should step down and Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe should do the same as he has no mandate to hold that position.",
        "Therefore, he states that the Sri Lanka Freedom Party's view is that the President and the Prime Minister should immediately resign from their positions and an all-party government should act immediately to solve the country's problems. . (R)"
      ],
